This paper discusses the integration of machine learning frameworks with hardware realization, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of low-precision representation and approximate arithmetic operations, which is a topic of interest in the field of Computer Architecture (cs.AR) and Emerging Technologies (cs.ET). Finally, the paper discusses the design space exploration for efficient hardware realization, which is a topic of interest in the field of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
